Package: Decant
Title: Benchmark-First Toolkit for Ambient RNA Decontamination Research
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Kushal Raj", "Roy", email = "kushalrajroy1@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4664-7462"))
Description: A research scaffold for developing and HONESTLY evaluating ambient
    RNA decontamination methods for single-cell and single-nucleus RNA-seq.
    Ships a ground-truth simulator, a global-soup baseline (the assumption used
    by SoupX and DecontX), a structured-soup experimental method, a
    mass-conserving correction step that cannot fabricate counts, and a metric
    suite mirroring the published benchmarks. The design principle is
    benchmark-first: a method is not added to the claims until the harness can
    show, against ground truth, that it earns its place. NOTE: name "Decant" is
    a working placeholder and must be checked against CRAN/Bioconductor/GitHub
    before any release.
